{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/diagnosis/differential-diagnosis/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"586d5e98-ed70-5f18-87b4-4725205a7deb","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 6b8330d5-1b79-493e-80b6-3101ad634eab --><h2>What else might it be?</h2><!-- end field 6b8330d5-1b79-493e-80b6-3101ad634eab -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 4f3927e9-4fbc-426f-8916-79f988b4fbf2 --><!-- begin field 24c08937-5951-46b8-9b4d-9a564dde5264 --><ul><li><strong>Alternative diagnoses which may present similarly to cow's milk allergy include:</strong><ul><li>Food intolerance (a non-immune adverse reaction), for example lactose intolerance caused by an inability to digest and absorb dietary lactose.<ul><li>Symptoms of lactose intolerance may overlap with those of non-IgE-mediated cow's milk allergy if there is <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/background-information/complications/\">cow&#39;s milk-induced enteropathy</a>, and may present with abdominal pain, bloating, and explosive diarrhoea typically 30–60 minutes following ingestion of lactose-containing foods.</li><li>Congenital lactase deficiency is very rare, does not usually manifest before 5 years of age, and is seen in small populations in Finland and Russia, for example.</li><li>Acquired or secondary lactose intolerance is usually transient and may occur with mucosal damage due to underlying gut conditions, such as following gastroenteritis. See the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/gastroenteritis/\">Gastroenteritis</a> for more information.</li></ul></li><li>Other food allergies (such as egg, soya protein, or wheat allergy) or allergies to other substances (such as animal dander, moulds, and dust). See the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/food-allergy/\">Food allergy</a> for more information.</li><li>Colic — see the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/colic-infantile/\">Colic - infantile</a> for more information.</li><li>Gastro-oesophageal reflux disease (GORD) — see the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/gord-in-children/\">GORD in children</a> for more information.</li><li>Crohn's disease — see the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/crohns-disease/\">Crohn&#39;s disease</a> for more information.</li><li>Coeliac disease — see the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/coeliac-disease/\">Coeliac disease</a> for more information.</li><li>Constipation — see the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/constipation-in-children/\">Constipation in children</a> for more information.</li><li>Ulcerative colitis — see the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/ulcerative-colitis/\">Ulcerative colitis</a> for more information.</li><li>Pancreatic insufficiency (such as in cystic fibrosis).</li><li>Infection (for example urinary tract infection) — see the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/urinary-tract-infection-children/\">Urinary tract infection - children</a> for more information.</li><li>Anatomical abnormalities, such as Meckel's diverticulum, intussusception, malrotation of the gut.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 24c08937-5951-46b8-9b4d-9a564dde5264 --><!-- end item 4f3927e9-4fbc-426f-8916-79f988b4fbf2 -->","topic":{"id":"a5282e12-9e0e-5a93-bf1e-c47cb44993b6","topicId":"055e8853-0668-4ee8-bef5-d86e8a39b416","topicName":"Cow's milk allergy in children","slug":"cows-milk-allergy-in-children","lastRevised":"Last revised in December 2019","chapters":[{"id":"e95ad3f8-8ddd-57bd-8fe1-a01a59402ca1","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"fceefe8b-f1a1-54cb-add7-5660134a61f9","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"ff117841-0d0c-5d1f-ad22-a2d8db741006","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"0a17cde7-a3cc-580f-a5ec-e74a03694b87","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"e8251ee6-b8da-567a-b543-5efa4c24f074","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"5cd1ea49-3964-5480-beb5-1208ab83ecb4","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"6737a350-b49d-5d33-a999-d2a5f41c7f48","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"bb1f8ca2-c855-56ee-bc57-4b1b77c9a276","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"296bbdac-c210-5305-8b31-aabc917df09f","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"5c4984e6-3f82-5632-9d43-2766ecbdec62","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"52bb5ec1-cd13-5a6e-a889-5e1d7a9ffcf6","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"92a5493f-38a6-5d89-a3e6-bcf0d7bfa1d6","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"8bb88e63-0cf4-5025-8dd3-1041e3b9d9ea","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"ec87042d-84e0-5a22-97eb-f9c346e5f3de","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"62433689-0bf5-54f1-a4c2-61d6274cdd19","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"},{"id":"99c10d89-9bd7-5a68-ba37-37973a5b10d4","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"8ef82df6-42bc-5a14-9b57-254620a2b8aa","slug":"risk-factors","fullItemName":"Risk factors"},{"id":"986684f6-12eb-5097-b456-a4a93d13e8df","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"},{"id":"be406e14-2076-5909-8906-48b6811961c8","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"}]},{"id":"25997383-2b89-5120-b436-f78f553f71a5","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"40d0f3d9-d912-537d-87c5-b3640e611d04","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},{"id":"2ebab214-a599-539f-ae72-55b67692fa41","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment"},{"id":"586d5e98-ed70-5f18-87b4-4725205a7deb","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"}]},{"id":"76847d5d-24bd-5dc8-9e92-c6b0890604de","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"3b931251-98f4-5554-b841-9a3066fb9d2a","slug":"suspected-cows-milk-allergy","fullItemName":"Scenario: Suspected cow's milk allergy"},{"id":"c08df731-7d31-540e-b7dd-58b4606316cc","slug":"confirmed-non-ige-mediated-cows-milk-allergy","fullItemName":"Scenario: Confirmed non-IgE-mediated cow's milk allergy"}]},{"id":"c9a37070-6475-56bf-b6e4-a4b75bdcb888","fullItemName":"Prescribing information","slug":"prescribing-information","subChapters":[{"id":"dec41209-5401-5f94-b2d8-acdbcc570995","slug":"antihistamines","fullItemName":"Antihistamines"}]},{"id":"582c6a43-d7ef-548b-bdef-e89a48b4d00c","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"998056ba-a465-5255-ad48-11dce2f00add","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"2ff6786c-3e69-5e28-b3e1-65b80a6e4dff","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"b656a2b3-ec81-5ad9-bada-358c550dcb41","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"a22b091c-0a22-5881-8f67-ef85da859ab7","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"af6d7d62-42c6-5ce2-be6c-f07386664122","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"2769d864-70a1-54c7-a684-6d21c7f45b79","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"24227540-66cf-5a28-ac25-cf52ba9aad4e","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"25997383-2b89-5120-b436-f78f553f71a5","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"c0e8ab8c-a55d-52e2-aa7a-206923d51ad8","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-f67","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field bd24fc8b-2cc7-4a0b-b320-a76d00847c4e --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field bd24fc8b-2cc7-4a0b-b320-a76d00847c4e -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item f67ec353-86be-4511-83d1-a76d00847af2 --><!-- begin field 675f48ec-cdbf-427c-8ea4-a76d00847c4e --><p>This information is based on the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) clinical guideline <em>Food allergy in under 19s: assessment and diagnosis</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">NICE, 2018</a>], the British Society for Allergy and Clinical Immunology (BSACI) publication <em>BSACI guideline for the diagnosis and management of cow's milk allergy</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Luyt et al, 2014</a>], the European Academy of Allergy and Clinical Immunology (EAACI) publication <em>Diagnosis and management of non‐IgE gastrointestinal allergies in breastfed infants - an EAACI Position Paper</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Meyer, 2019</a>], and expert opinion in a review article on cow's milk allergy in children [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Ludman et al, 2013</a>], on non-IgE-mediated cow's milk allergy [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Venter et al, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Venter, 2017</a>], and on lactose intolerance [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Swagerty et al, 2002</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Heine, 2017</a>].</p><ul><li>Expert opinion in a review article notes that the severity of symptoms and resistance to treatment may suggest a diagnosis of cow's milk allergy rather than isolated conditions such as gastro-oesophageal reflux disease (GORD) or atopic eczema [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/cows-milk-allergy-in-children/references/\">Ludman et al, 2013</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 675f48ec-cdbf-427c-8ea4-a76d00847c4e --><!-- end item f67ec353-86be-4511-83d1-a76d00847af2 -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}